00:30.000 --> 00:31.120
Oh, God.

00:31.200 --> 00:33.479
How are you, Richard? Hot enough for you?

00:34.238 --> 00:35.558
Yeah.

00:42.555 --> 00:44.234
Hey, what are you doing?

00:44.834 --> 00:47.713
You dummy, why don't you watch
where you are going?

01:14.581 --> 01:16.821
Does this look like 10:00, or like 10:30?

01:16.901 --> 01:19.020
- Morning, Richard!
- Good morning.

01:19.060 --> 01:21.259
- You are a half hour late.
- Only a half hour?

01:21.339 --> 01:24.257
I am usually 45 minutes late.
I am early today.

01:24.897 --> 01:26.057
I see.

01:32.454 --> 01:35.253
- Are you going to join me today or what?
- Coming.

01:37.172 --> 01:39.371
Give me your money and your wallets.

01:39.611 --> 01:42.010
Get your ass out of here. It is too hot.

01:48.527 --> 01:51.966
Color me old-fashioned, Rich,
but I just love the park on a Sunday.

01:52.046 --> 01:55.964
I would love it more if we didn't have
to work today. Come on, let's go.

02:06.920 --> 02:09.439
Let me open that for you, all right?

02:34.908 --> 02:36.907
Hot enough for you, Larry?

02:37.307 --> 02:39.746
No, Harris, why don't you turn up the heat?

02:39.826 --> 02:42.105
Okay. I'll tell the engineer.

02:46.183 --> 02:49.582
Cheap bastards. Turn off
the air conditioning on the weekends.

03:13.812 --> 03:17.051
- Let's go to the beach.
- No.

03:17.410 --> 03:21.049
- We are going to be here our whole lives.
- Yeah, I am afraid so.

03:25.367 --> 03:27.926
- I am going to the beach!
- Give me those papers.

03:28.006 --> 03:30.405
- The papers are going to the beach.
- We aren't going.

03:30.485 --> 03:32.524
You want these?
You're coming to the beach.

03:32.604 --> 03:35.283
- I guess we are going to the beach.
- Wilson at the line.

03:36.882 --> 03:39.281
That was beautiful. Replay.

03:42.200 --> 03:43.760
Give me those papers!

03:47.238 --> 03:51.236
- You think it's safe to go in the water?
- No, better not.

03:52.236 --> 03:56.394
- You just ate. You might get cramps.
- I'll risk it.

04:05.031 --> 04:07.949
{y:i}We'll get back to you with more tunes,
{y:i}but first we'll hear...

04:08.029 --> 04:10.109
{y:i}the latest from Weather Central.

04:10.189 --> 04:13.187
{y:i}- What is happening out there, buddy?
{y:i}- Sizzle, sizzle...

04:13.267 --> 04:15.706
{y:i}as the Big Apple becomes the Baked Apple.

04:15.826 --> 04:17.545
{y:i}You better believe that these are...

04:17.625 --> 04:19.545
Oh, Christ. Will you shut that thing off?

04:19.625 --> 04:21.664
{y:i}... continues before Labor Day weekend.

04:21.704 --> 04:26.142
{y:i}It is going to be the four "H's":
{y:i}Hot, humid, hazy, and horrible.

04:28.741 --> 04:30.940
This sucks. I am so unhappy.

04:31.740 --> 04:35.578
- We should be at a real beach.
- There are no more real beaches.

04:35.618 --> 04:39.576
I mean we could go to Jones Beach
and float around in the hospital waste.

04:39.656 --> 04:41.655
Then again Coney Island is always real nice.

04:41.735 --> 04:45.134
We could go there and watch the fish
disintegrate in front of our eyes.

04:45.214 --> 04:49.372
Wait a minute. Wait a goddamn...
Hold the phone, buddy! I got it!

04:49.412 --> 04:51.851
I got the $2 million. Where are your pages?

04:51.891 --> 04:53.451
Get your pages.

04:53.491 --> 04:56.809
Oh, my God!
You are not going to believe what you see!

04:57.649 --> 04:59.448
- Okay.
- Turn to Page 28.

05:01.847 --> 05:02.887
Right after 27.

05:04.766 --> 05:06.165
- Got it.
- All right? You got it?

05:06.245 --> 05:08.364
I want you to turn to Page 41 now.

05:10.204 --> 05:11.723
- I got it.
- Check out line 18.

05:11.763 --> 05:12.803
- Okay?
- Yeah.

05:12.842 --> 05:13.962
- You see it?
- I see it.

05:14.202 --> 05:15.801
What about it?

05:16.801 --> 05:19.200
You are such a stupid piece of rat shit.

05:19.440 --> 05:20.919
Hot!

05:20.999 --> 05:23.558
- Watch your step!
- I am being barbecued here!

05:23.878 --> 05:27.516
All right. Okay. All right, buddy
I am going to explain it to you real slow.

05:27.596 --> 05:28.636
- Good.
- Okay.

05:28.716 --> 05:32.354
There's more than one check issued
on the same life insurance policy claim.

05:32.394 --> 05:36.193
One in December of '87, another in
April of '88, and two more in June.

05:36.273 --> 05:38.232
- Making any sense?
- Yeah, he died four times.

05:38.312 --> 05:40.991
Yes. According to this, he died four times.

05:41.071 --> 05:43.550
So somebody screwed up.
It wasn't us. Was it?

05:43.630 --> 05:45.589
No. It wasn't us.

05:45.669 --> 05:48.428
Don't you see?
We just uncovered a $2 million error.

05:48.508 --> 05:51.386
We're going to be heroes.
We're going up the corporate ladder.

05:51.466 --> 05:53.865
- This is good for me.
- Yes, this is good for you.

05:53.905 --> 05:57.464
- It's good for me, too.
- I'll tell Lomax first thing in the morning.

05:57.544 --> 05:59.703
- What page is it?
- No, Larry. Let me tell him.

05:59.783 --> 06:02.062
- We'll both tell him.
- Okay. Great!

06:09.579 --> 06:11.298
There is what's-her-name.

06:23.333 --> 06:24.773
Stop staring at her.

06:24.853 --> 06:26.732
You've not shut up about her
for two months.

06:26.812 --> 06:29.691
- Ask her out already, will you?
- No. I don't know what to say.

06:29.731 --> 06:31.890
She's a summer intern.
She'll be gone in a week.

06:31.930 --> 06:33.129
No, I've no idea what to say.

06:33.209 --> 06:36.368
- Say "Hi, I want to go out with you."
- I can't say that.

06:36.848 --> 06:38.127
Why not?

06:38.207 --> 06:40.006
Because there are too many people around.

06:40.086 --> 06:42.525
It's New York City.
There are always too many people.

06:42.605 --> 06:44.125
Excuse me, miss.

06:50.002 --> 06:51.402
Oh, shit.

06:52.041 --> 06:53.441
Good weekend, Bob?

06:59.078 --> 07:01.317
- You going to say something?
- Shut up.

07:02.517 --> 07:04.596
- You are blowing it.
- Shut...

07:05.556 --> 07:07.395
Please, shut up, all right?

07:14.192 --> 07:15.512
Thank you.

07:23.028 --> 07:24.108
Okay.

07:24.828 --> 07:26.387
Try witty.

07:26.787 --> 07:29.306
Say, "You know what would look
good on you?"

07:29.746 --> 07:33.024
- "Me." Huh?
- Oh, please.

07:33.184 --> 07:35.583
- Richard, that is a very good line.
- Enough, look...

07:35.663 --> 07:38.462
- if I wanted to talk to her, I'll talk to her.
- Talk to her.

07:38.502 --> 07:40.301
- Would you talk to her?
- Would you stop?

07:40.541 --> 07:42.300
- You want me to talk to her?
- Yes.

07:42.340 --> 07:43.860
Okay. Shut up.

07:44.499 --> 07:45.819
Excuse me.

07:55.415 --> 07:57.214
My aunt is very sick.

08:03.372 --> 08:04.451
What?

08:06.410 --> 08:07.650
Nothing.

08:17.366 --> 08:18.605
I don't believe this, she's...

08:18.685 --> 08:21.364
Now, don't flagellate yourself
over this, Richard.

08:21.444 --> 08:23.923
It was a very good effort.
You'll get her next time.

08:24.003 --> 08:26.762
Why did I just say that?
Larry, I don't even have an aunt.

08:26.842 --> 08:28.041
So what?

08:28.681 --> 08:30.440
Anything going on?

08:30.720 --> 08:32.200
There are these messages.

08:32.280 --> 08:35.198
And you are late for
the creative sales meeting, Mr. Lomax.

08:35.238 --> 08:37.876
- Excuse us, Mr. Lomax.
- Let me get that, sir.

08:38.397 --> 08:39.636
Sammy. Hank. How are you?

08:39.717 --> 08:41.076
Richard Parker, sir.

08:41.116 --> 08:42.835
- Larry Wilson.
- Whatever.

08:43.115 --> 08:45.274
There's nothing from a Doreena,
a Martha, Judy?

08:45.314 --> 08:47.713
- No.
- Well, that's their tough luck.

08:47.753 --> 08:49.073
- Excuse us, Mr. Lomax.
- What?

08:49.153 --> 08:51.232
There's something
we would like to show you.

08:51.312 --> 08:54.630
Wait. It's Monday morning.
After lunch, right?

08:54.750 --> 08:56.470
Quite a bit after lunch.

08:56.909 --> 08:57.909
Shoo.

09:20.580 --> 09:22.059
Yeah, I got it, FranÃ§ois.

09:25.458 --> 09:26.537
That's $2.

09:29.096 --> 09:30.176
Rich.

09:30.256 --> 09:31.735
Look at Lomax.

09:31.855 --> 09:33.014
God.

09:33.854 --> 09:36.373
My God. Look at her.

09:36.453 --> 09:37.453
My God.

09:38.732 --> 09:40.411
Jesus. That guy.

09:40.971 --> 09:44.090
Beautiful apartment. House at the beach.

09:44.410 --> 09:47.169
Babes. A boat. A car.

09:47.528 --> 09:50.887
Do you know how much it costs
to park a car in Manhattan every month?

09:50.927 --> 09:54.765
- More than my rent.
- I mean, it's only fair.

09:54.845 --> 09:57.884
His car is a bit bigger than your apartment.

09:58.004 --> 10:00.643
So my apartment is small. It's dark.

10:00.883 --> 10:04.082
It's hot. It's in a high-crime area.
Beats living with Mom and Dad.

10:04.161 --> 10:07.480
All right. Enough.
It's just until I can afford something decent.

10:07.560 --> 10:10.119
Something without
wall-to-wall cockroaches.

10:12.558 --> 10:15.797
All I have to do is just keep
setting my goals and working hard...

10:15.837 --> 10:17.236
- I'll be fine.
- You are so naive.

10:17.476 --> 10:19.075
- I'm sorry.
- Excuse me.

10:19.835 --> 10:22.274
Go ahead. Oh, God.

10:22.354 --> 10:24.313
I hope your aunt feels better.

10:25.912 --> 10:27.072
- What?
- I said...

10:27.112 --> 10:29.391
She said, "I hope your aunt feels better."

10:29.471 --> 10:32.550
My aunt? The sick aunt. Yes, she is fine.

10:32.630 --> 10:33.909
They thought it was...

10:33.989 --> 10:36.508
Either get on the elevator or get off.

10:37.588 --> 10:38.787
I'll be back.

10:43.345 --> 10:45.624
And I lose again.

10:45.704 --> 10:48.583
I won. I have a date.

10:49.543 --> 10:50.862
- You are kidding.
- No.

10:50.942 --> 10:54.021
Gwen and I, Thursday night,
8:00 p.m., dinner.

10:54.061 --> 10:57.379
- Fabulous.
- It was the clumsy approach. It worked.

10:57.819 --> 11:00.298
You are going to want
to borrow my apartment.

11:00.378 --> 11:02.857
No, but thank you. That's sweet.

11:02.937 --> 11:05.656
But I can't do that to you. Thank you.

11:06.735 --> 11:10.174
If she finds out you live with your folks,
you will embarrass yourself.

11:10.254 --> 11:12.813
Yeah, I know, but I can't do that to you.

11:16.891 --> 11:18.970
It is the cockroaches, isn't it?

11:19.650 --> 11:22.169
- Well...
- They scatter when the lights go on.

11:24.208 --> 11:26.727
{y:i}Mr. Parker, Mr. Lomax will see you now.

11:27.007 --> 11:28.207
I feel lucky.

11:31.405 --> 11:34.684
No, I only want the Maserati
if it comes in that jet black.

11:34.684 --> 11:36.163
Look, if you can't do it for me...

11:36.243 --> 11:39.202
I'll just have to take my business
to another dealer.

11:39.682 --> 11:40.761
Yeah.

11:41.641 --> 11:44.560
So paint it! I mean how hard
can this whole thing be?

11:44.640 --> 11:45.799
Right.

11:46.839 --> 11:48.798
All right. See, that's better.

11:48.838 --> 11:51.637
See how easy it is to do business with me?

11:54.196 --> 11:56.555
No trade. Strictly cash.

11:56.795 --> 11:58.114
Right.

11:58.954 --> 12:00.313
All right. Good.

12:05.511 --> 12:07.710
Gentlemen, what have you got for me?

12:10.589 --> 12:13.308
As you may or may not know, Mr. Lomax...

12:13.388 --> 12:17.506
Larry and I have been, I mean, working.

12:17.586 --> 12:20.305
- Where is he going?
- I don't know.

12:21.384 --> 12:23.344
What are we supposed to do?

12:24.663 --> 12:27.262
Bet that thing moves, huh? Jesus.

12:27.342 --> 12:29.901
- Put that back.
- It's a beautiful boat.

12:40.337 --> 12:41.896
You gentlemen were saying...

12:41.976 --> 12:43.175
Yes, well.

12:43.255 --> 12:45.135
As you might have heard...

12:45.934 --> 12:50.053
Larry and I have been reprogramming
the accounts on the new computer system.

12:50.133 --> 12:51.732
- Right.
- Thanks.

12:53.251 --> 12:54.891
Sir, it's a very big job.

12:54.971 --> 12:57.250
A big job. We have been working hard.

12:57.330 --> 12:58.329
A very big job.

12:58.409 --> 13:00.728
I've been at it for quite some time.
Weekends also.

13:00.808 --> 13:02.887
- Weekends, late, and...
- Why don't you show him?

13:02.967 --> 13:03.967
Thank you.

13:04.007 --> 13:05.886
We've got something
you should know about.

13:05.966 --> 13:08.565
- Got them both there?
- Yes. Page 28 and 41.

13:19.960 --> 13:22.359
You sure these figures are accurate?

13:22.759 --> 13:24.158
- Yes.
- Positive.

13:24.238 --> 13:25.918
Yes, sir, Mr. Lomax.

13:28.557 --> 13:29.716
Bernie.

13:34.194 --> 13:35.714
Call me Bernie.

13:35.794 --> 13:38.073
I mean my father is Mr. Lomax, right?

13:46.989 --> 13:48.748
Okay, Bernie.

13:49.188 --> 13:53.626
- Yes, it's all there in black and white.
- We both worked on this one, Bern.

13:54.506 --> 13:55.465
"E."

13:56.105 --> 13:57.465
Bernie.

13:59.184 --> 14:01.903
- Papers.
- Right here, Bernie.

14:03.142 --> 14:05.381
If anything has to go,
I am glad it's my vision...

14:05.461 --> 14:08.540
and not the old joystick,
you know what I mean?

14:10.299 --> 14:12.338
That's computer ink, sir.

14:16.577 --> 14:18.776
Oh, no, you are wrong. Look.

14:19.255 --> 14:23.454
There are multiple checks issued
because there were several policies written.

14:23.494 --> 14:26.053
You didn't take into consideration
that it's normal...

14:26.133 --> 14:29.131
especially when using
a fluctuating COL index to combine...

14:29.211 --> 14:33.090
Iook here, a package containing
short-term and straight life policies...

14:33.130 --> 14:35.009
in an overall insurance portfolio.

14:35.089 --> 14:37.208
Now you are wasting my time.

14:42.166 --> 14:44.565
Richard worked on that part, sir.

14:45.645 --> 14:48.163
That is true, Bernie.

14:48.723 --> 14:53.001
But if you were to look at the back page,
where the policy indexes are...

14:53.081 --> 14:55.440
you'll notice that the remaining policies...

14:55.480 --> 14:59.639
are dated after
the policy holder died, Bernie.

14:59.839 --> 15:01.358
You are right.

15:01.878 --> 15:04.477
You are absolutely right.
Gentlemen, this is good work.

15:04.557 --> 15:06.236
Very, very good work.

15:06.316 --> 15:07.915
Thank you, Bernie.

15:07.955 --> 15:10.914
I hate to say this, but it appears
as if somebody is trying...

15:10.954 --> 15:13.793
to defraud the company.
Perhaps we should check back records.

15:13.873 --> 15:16.472
Somebody tried to smoke it
past the wrong guy.

15:17.191 --> 15:18.551
No smoking.

15:18.951 --> 15:21.949
Gentlemen, how long have you two
been working here?

15:22.029 --> 15:24.428
- Nineteen months and a week.
- I am not really sure.

15:24.468 --> 15:27.187
- A little longer, I think.
- Longer? I was here before you.

15:27.267 --> 15:28.547
No, Richard. I trained you.

15:28.627 --> 15:31.466
I came here in January,
you came the end of May.

15:31.545 --> 15:33.105
I trained you.

15:33.185 --> 15:34.464
Whatever!

15:35.424 --> 15:38.303
What I am saying is that
I think there is a big future here...

15:38.383 --> 15:41.101
for a couple of bright fellows
like yourselves.

15:41.781 --> 15:42.901
Thank you.

15:42.981 --> 15:45.220
But I'd like to go over these numbers
with you...

15:45.300 --> 15:47.619
just to make sure
that you've gotten everything.

15:47.699 --> 15:50.737
The only trouble is if someone is trying to...

15:51.057 --> 15:53.256
like you said
"smoke it past the wrong guy"...

15:53.336 --> 15:55.575
I'd like to just keep it confidential.

15:55.615 --> 15:58.254
I mean there is no sense sending up
a bunch of red flags.

15:58.334 --> 15:59.494
No, absolutely not.

15:59.574 --> 16:01.453
If you would like, we'll work late.

16:01.493 --> 16:04.772
- Yes, I mean we'll work weekends.
- Weekends are very good for me.

16:04.852 --> 16:07.251
Weekends. Good idea.

16:07.650 --> 16:10.449
Give us plenty of time together,
no distractions.

16:10.569 --> 16:12.169
It is Labor Day.

16:15.847 --> 16:17.326
I got an idea.

16:19.925 --> 16:23.524
How would you two like to come
to my house at the beach?

16:23.644 --> 16:24.883
- Me?
- Us?

16:24.963 --> 16:26.643
Yeah. Hampton Island.

16:26.723 --> 16:29.401
Ever been there? Well, you will love it.

16:29.481 --> 16:31.720
When we're not working,
there are distractions.

16:31.800 --> 16:34.639
There are women, swimming,
boating, famous people.

16:37.878 --> 16:39.237
Well?

16:39.277 --> 16:40.317
- Love to!
- Okay.

16:40.397 --> 16:42.196
Good! It's settled.

16:42.836 --> 16:45.795
We are going to have a good time,
I guarantee.

16:45.875 --> 16:47.874
My secretary will write down
the directions...

16:47.914 --> 16:50.193
- give you the ferry schedule.
- The ferry schedule?

16:50.273 --> 16:53.551
It's the only way to get there,
unless you have a boat. I don't know.

16:53.631 --> 16:55.391
I have never even been on a boat.

16:55.471 --> 16:57.870
I was once on the Staten Island Ferry
with my folks...

16:57.950 --> 17:01.748
Whatever. You come out Friday night,
you'll have a great time, I guarantee it.

17:01.788 --> 17:04.787
I'll even drive you back to the city myself
on Monday. Okay?

17:04.867 --> 17:06.986
We don't know what to say, Bernie.

17:07.746 --> 17:09.944
You don't have to say anything.

17:10.105 --> 17:12.943
If you two uncovered what I think
you uncovered...

17:13.262 --> 17:16.742
old Bernie here owes you both a great deal.
I mean it sincerely.

17:16.821 --> 17:19.021
Now get out of here. Go on.

17:20.980 --> 17:22.419
He loves us.

17:22.739 --> 17:26.657
The man absolutely loves us.

17:28.777 --> 17:30.256
You have to kill them, Vito.

17:41.811 --> 17:44.050
Let me explain something to you.

17:44.810 --> 17:48.569
We don't do that anymore.
We are a corporation now.

17:49.528 --> 17:51.967
We are in the market. We invest.

17:52.007 --> 17:55.806
Real estate. Car rentals. Parking lots.

17:57.165 --> 17:59.404
Parking lots. That's good.

18:00.124 --> 18:03.043
- I understand that, but...
- Didn't I order the walnut dressing?

18:03.083 --> 18:05.442
- Yes, you did.
- Taste that.

18:07.081 --> 18:10.160
Does that taste
anything like walnut dressing? Tell me.

18:10.879 --> 18:13.198
This is the raspberry vinaigrette.

18:13.998 --> 18:16.677
Should I have Paulie go
and talk to the chef?

18:19.236 --> 18:22.794
This goddamn raspberry vinaigrette...

18:26.953 --> 18:28.512
Excuse me, Vito.

18:36.948 --> 18:39.667
I know how important food is to you,
I mean...

18:40.987 --> 18:42.866
But we've got a problem here.

18:43.706 --> 18:46.225
I give problems. I don't get problems.

18:51.582 --> 18:53.941
How do you propose to handle it?

18:53.981 --> 18:57.060
Let's make it a murder-suicide job. All right?

18:57.700 --> 18:59.059
Okay, gentlemen?

18:59.459 --> 19:02.898
I'll plant some money, fake a note,
and they can take the rap and...

19:02.978 --> 19:05.776
I won't even have to change the books.

19:06.096 --> 19:07.776
What do you think?

19:11.854 --> 19:14.173
I like it. It's creative.

19:17.891 --> 19:20.650
I am a little rusty. But it'll come back to me.

19:26.728 --> 19:27.847
Okay.

19:30.526 --> 19:33.165
- Do it.
- This is good.

19:33.285 --> 19:35.844
I mean this is really good. Good.

19:37.963 --> 19:41.402
I think we are going to have some fun.

19:46.040 --> 19:49.318
- I have to get going. I really do.
- What, no dessert?

19:49.838 --> 19:52.877
